        <prompt>The Scopes "Monkey" Trial of 1925 primarily concerned:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">The teaching of evolution in public schools</option>
            <option letter="b">Animal rights in laboratories</option>
            <option letter="c">Child labor laws</option>
            <option letter="d">Religious freedom in universities</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Scopes Trial centered on John Scopes, a Tennessee teacher charged with violating state law by teaching evolution. The trial became a dramatic confrontation between modernist and fundamentalist values, featuring William Jennings Bryan for the prosecution and Clarence Darrow for the defense. Though Scopes was convicted, the trial highlighted the growing tension between traditional religious beliefs and modern scientific education.</explanation>
